In [ ]:
#Assign data to 'AnnData' object
adatas = {}

samples = {"s1d1": "s1d1_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5",
           "s1d3": "s1d3_filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5"}
for sample_id, filename in samples.items():
    path = EXAMPLE_DATA.fetch(filename)
    sample_adata = sc.read_10x_h5(path)
    sample_adata.var_names_make_unique()
    adatas[sample_id] = sample_adata

adata = ad.concat(adatas, label="sample")

Quality Control¶

  • calculate_qc_metrics() QC metrics .
In [ ]:
#Define the prefixes of mitochondrial, ribosomal and hemoglobin genes 
adata.var["mt"] = adata.var_names.str.startswith("MT-") #mitochondrial genes
adata.var["ribo"] = adata.var_names.str.startswith(("RPS", "RPL")) #ribosomal genes
adata.var["hb"] = adata.var_names.str.contains("^HB[^(P)]") #hemoglobin genes
In [ ]:
#Quality control
sc.pp.calculate_qc_metrics(adata, qc_vars=["mt", "ribo", "hb"], inplace=True, log1p=True)
In [ ]:
#Visualize the QC result: "n_genes_by_counts", "total_counts", "pct_counts_mt"
sc.pl.violin(adata, ["n_genes_by_counts", "total_counts", "pct_counts_mt"], jitter=0.4, multi_panel=True)
  • QC . 1) Count matrix 2) total count 3) count
In [ ]:
#Visualize the QC result: all together
sc.pl.scatter(adata, "total_counts", "n_genes_by_counts", color="pct_counts_mt")

Normalization¶

  • normalization log plus one(log1p) transformation count depth scaling .
  • Coutn depth scaling "size facor" normalization .
    • Size factor median count depth, CP10K, CPM .
  • log1PF median count depth normalization .

#Backup count data
adata.layers["counts"] = adata.X.copy()
In [ ]:
#Normalizing to median total counts

sc.pp.log1p(adata)
